#      echoes a hardcoded placeholder string "ghs_DRYRUN_<timestamp>" to prove
#      the wrapper resolved its args WITHOUT touching the real broker/GitHub.
#      It only ever matches the scanner's ghs_ (GitHub App installation token)
#      prefix because of the literal "DRYRUN" text, not a minted credential —
#      no real token is ever assigned to this string. Verified: this is the
#      ONLY secret-prefix hit in the file (working tree + both git-history
#      revisions); independently re-checked against the raw source line.
ghs_DRYRUN_

